tip.text: Favourite skewers are the liver and heart. Try the chicken namba!
Huge bookstore and stationery supplies, with wider range and friendlier prices compared to art Friend. Managed to find all the stationeries I wanted here.

formattedAddress: Levels 2 to 5, Bras Basah Complex (231 Bain St.)

tip.text: 鸡头chicken rice is very good.

venue.name: Clementi 448 Market & Food Centre 金文泰巴刹小販中心

tip.text: Eat the chicken skin. So bad but so good. No regrets. Try the beef kuay Teow too!
Beautiful resort just a stone's throw away from civilisation. Highlights were the rain shower, king sized bed, hot tub, Highly recommended will definitely come back again.

formattedAddress: 55000 Kuala Lumpur, Federal Territory of Kuala Lum

tip.text: Fish soup with Long queue is very good. Tried the fish head soup which was excellent. Generous portions. Worth the wait.

venue.name: Clementi 448 Market & Food Centre 金文泰巴刹小販中心

tip.text: Top favourites are 1) Claypot rice. Always get the one with salted fish 2) fried kuay Teow 3) satay and top everything off with beer.
Had the Shao Xin wine chicken with rice. It was nutritious and tasty. The belachan was not kidding.
Simple, healthy and tasty lunch.

venue.name: Clementi 448 Market & Food Centre 金文泰巴刹小販中心

tip.text: Food was 7.5/10. Good. The last layer was really sinful and awesome coz you get to add all kinds of junk. Service was 10/10. Friendly and attentive staff (:
Come for the egg tarts! Come in the late afternoon to skip the queue. Just have drinks and pastries.

venue.name: Tai Cheong Bakery 泰昌餅家

tip.text: One of the best China Chinese hotpots in Singapore. Thick slices of meat. Good quality ingredients. Abundant selection of sauces and to top it all of, fancy dragon pots! Must try!

venue.name: Spicy House Restaurant 辣府火锅

tip.text: Marinated chunks of seafood. I had the sashimi bowl. Pick the multi grain rice for a healthier option.  Not the best rice bowl I've had, but it's good for the price. Healthy and comforting
Really good home made pastas done well. Try the marrow with tagliata. Yum yum.

formattedAddress: #05-03/#06-02, National Gallery Singapore (1 St Andrews Rd)

tip.text: It's good. Add the dry chili powder and fish sauce to the soup for an extra kick!

formattedAddress: See Lam Hern Coffeeshop (449 Clementi Ave. 3. #01-211.)

tip.text: Had the original with soy powder, rice cakes and almond flakes. The rice cakes were really good one of the better bingsus in Singapore. Minus point for the place being Super cold.

formattedAddress: #L1-CA2, Bukit Timah Plaza (1 Jalan Anak Bukit)

venue.name: Bing Go Jung Korean Dessert House

tip.text: Great place to bring a date. Beautiful old architecture combined with beautiful art pieces. Try the Chilli crab pasta it's a good twist of modern and local taste.
My hotel was just around the corner. This place looks so nasty but the food is so good. Highly recommend the curry fishballs and the 车仔面. Pigs blood is a must have, try the satay soup too! V tasty
Sorry, would not rate this as #1 cozy in HK. Coffee was good. Space was alright.
The queue was insanely Long so I did a take out. Had it in the hotel room with Kirin beer. Roasted goose was superb. Try the honey char Siew too! Highly recommended 👍🏻👍🏻

location.address: G/F, Po Wah Commercial Centre, 226-226A Hennessy Rd
formattedAddress: G/F, Po Wah Commercial Centre, 226-226A Hennessy Rd

tip.text: Best Szechuan hotpot I had in Hong Kong. Mala soup base was spicy and very very fragrant. Highly recommended. Sauce station is a plus point!
Sliced fatty beef was delicious. Ma la and also the tomato soup base was very tasty. Everything else was meh and the service was appalling. Dumplings were too big and took forever to cook.

contact.facebookName: 北斗翁頂尊火鍋料理 /  釣魚翁燒鵝．海鮮飯店

venue.name: Budaoweng Hotpot Cuisine 不倒翁中日火鍋料理 (不倒翁中日火鍋料理)

tip.text: Good quality coffee. Fragrant, strong bodied and smooth. Friendly and helpful staff too.
Reasonably priced good quality dim sum. Other than the usual Siew Mai and Har Gao, I recommend the stuffed Chili, the spare ribs with pumpkin and also the chicken feet.

venue.name: DimDimSum Dim Sum Specialty Store 點點心點心專門店 (點點心點心專門店)

tip.text: Introduced my family to this place and they went back almost every night. They cray. Ginger lovers please order the hot ginger steamed milk. Warms your belly. Purists go for the original. 👍🏻

venue.name: Yee Shun Dairy Company 港澳義順牛奶公司 (港澳義順牛奶公司)

tip.text: Had the fish belly with "第” congee. Meaning mixed pork - including pork balls, kidney, stomach, etc. Congee was very flavourful though plain looking. Saw a lot of local uncles and aunties eating too.

venue.name: Sang Kee Congee & Noodle (生記粥麵)

tip.text: Beautiful magical place. Not as big as the rest of the Disneylands but just as awesome if you manage your expectations. Go in the afternoon after lunch and stay till late for the fireworks.

contact.facebookName: 香港迪士尼樂園 | Hong Kong Disneyland

venue.name: Hong Kong Disneyland (香港迪士尼樂園)

tip.text: Truly beautiful views all the way up. Steep yes, but very manageable. Just take it one step a time. Caution: I had a horrid sunburn so do apply sunblock!
Fries are good with coke for a mid day perk me up to feed your inner child. I mean it's Disneyland anyway, indulge yourself.

location.address: Tomorrowland, Hong Kong Disneyland, Penny's Bay, Lantau Island
formattedAddress: Tomorrowland, Hong Kong Disneyland, Penny's Bay, Lantau Island

tip.text: Tsukemen is very good. Always come here after work for drinks and light bites. The mini dons despite their size, are quite satisfying taste wise.
The food is good. Promising new restaurant. Give it a try!
Beautiful Japanese garden. Seems touristy but do enjoy a cup of matcha and Japanese dessert by the pond. The garden is also filled with maple trees, best time to visit would be in autumn.
Route E was challenging and fun. Covers both local area and tourist spots. Lots of hills but you can always push your bike up like I did. Guides give a good explanation on the various destinations.

venue.name: Tokyo Great Cycling Tour 事務局

tip.text: Had the udon in a pot with miso. The photo doesn't do the dish justice. Combination of hot soup + smooth noodles really warms the stomach and heart on a chilly day. Highly recommended, worth the queue

venue.name: Tsurutontan (つるとんたん BIS TOKYO)

tip.text: This is a very fancy tsurutontan. You get a good view of Ginza. My Favourite is always the grated yam udon with tempura on the side. Ask for the thinner udon, it's my personal favourite!

venue.name: TsuruTonTan (つるとんたん 銀座 UDON NOODLE Brasserie)

tip.text: Beautiful contemporary museum in the heart of the city. Go up to experience magnificent views of Tokyo and if you're lucky on a clear day, may even get to see Mount Fuji!

formattedAddress: 六本木6-10-1 (六本木ヒルズ森タワー 53F)
location.crossStreet: 六本木ヒルズ森タワー 53F

tip.text: Floors and floors of Super cool merchandise and display. Truly a unique shopping experience and a must visit for people working in retail industry or if you just have dough to burn.
Went there for breakfast at 8:30am. No queue.  The dipping sauce is really flavourful and noodles al dente. Once finished, dilute the sauce with some stock, add Yuzu powder. Refreshing soupy ending.

formattedAddress: 丸の内1-9-1 (東京駅一番街 B1F 東京ラーメンストリート)
location.crossStreet: 東京駅一番街 B1F 東京ラーメンストリート

tip.text: Meat glorious meat. Get the 14800 yen set which feeds 3-4 pax, and add some side dishes. Order a few rounds of beer. Combination is magical. For the quality it's totally worth the  price.

venue.name: 俺の焼肉 銀座9丁目店

tip.text: Had the soy latte, dark blend. I actually didn't know it's by Starbucks until I got there. Was slightly disappointed at first. After experiencing, was pleasantly surprised by the concept and novelty.

venue.name: Neighborhood and Coffee (Neighborhood and Coffee 代沢5丁目店)

tip.text: Quaint shopping street. Good for buying some local produce and wares. Do venture into the smaller alleyways. There is a store selling home made tofu.

venue.name: Yanaka Ginza Shotengai (谷中銀座商店街)

tip.text: I tried the tuna avocado rice bowl. Looks good and tastes good! Fresh ingredients, hipster experience.

Save half the appetiser for the end. Mix the wasabi into the sauce. Pour over kaisendon. Enjoy. After, ask for soup & more rice (if u didn't save 1/2 frm before). Enjoy once more. Best kaisendon ever.
Gambas is a must have. Filled with garlicky goodness. Also try the paella with meat and seafood. In addition to the seafood Unami, the sausage makes the dish extra fragrant!

location.crossStreet: Up from Tourist Center, close to Police Station
location.address: Remedios street, Sitio Manggayad, Boracay Island
formattedAddress: Remedios street, Sitio Manggayad, Boracay Island (Up from Tourist Center, close to Police Station)

tip.text: The Hor fun is amazing. With beef, soya sauce chicken or curry. Try it!
Limited menu offering compared to Palais. Had the torched salmon from the specials. It was beautifully plated. Flavours were balanced well and loved how the salmon was framed with sprigs of green.

formattedAddress: Level 3, Paragon Shopping Centre (290 Orchard Rd)

tip.text: The pulled pork tacos were okay. Beef taco was good. But the tacos were really wet and dripping with water from what I assumed was the raw veggies? Frozen margarita was Super sweet and not strong.
I had the curry fish head, butter paneer, cauliflower. They were so good. Given that the location is at Dempsey I expected it to be very touristy and expensive. Nope. Authentic Indian food.
One of the best places to take over the dead end of rail mall. Thosai was good, crisp in the right places, generous and super affordable at $1.60. Great vibe and atmosphere.

formattedAddress: 396 Upper Bukit Timah Rd (The Rail Mall)

tip.text: Steamed chicken is constantly good. Ginger sauce is da bomb. This branch seems to have a lot more dim sum options. Will be back to try that out!

venue.name: Soup Restaurant Teahouse 三盅兩件茶楼

tip.text: Ribs were tasty and tender. Mussels were really good with garlic bread. Alcohol selection is good. Overall a very nice place in the west to just chill over hearty food and drinks.
The rice is not Japanese rice. The food tastes decent but going by Jap standards this place doesn't cut it.
When they say it's going to be spicy they are not kidding! The pickled cucumbers are pretty authentic. Try the seafood fish noodles!
Had the Nasi goreng belachan with crispy chicken and added a sunny side up egg. The food was decent and the view and ambience is amazing. Great place.
Its no three michelin star Asian restaurant but honestly it wasn't too bad for airport food. I mean, brown rice, teriyaki chicken and fresh greens. Simple and comforting meal for any traveller.
Steak and sous vide egg = perfect marriage ❤️❤️❤️❤️
The food is not very authentic Japanese as some yakitoris have mayo on them. That aside, the food is decent and the atmosphere is lively.
Try the Homemade mushroom tofu. So soft and flavourful! Done really well. The flounder skirt and Uni sushi was really fatty and decadent!
Yes please try the Bak kut Teh Claypot set. Add $1 for mushroom and another $2 for Mee Sua ❤️❤️ remember to return your tray!

formattedAddress: JTC LaunchPad @ one-North (73A Ayer Rajah Crescent)

tip.text: Tried the Salmon says. The salmon in my roll was like the amount of avocado in the pic. And there was shredded carrot as fillers for the salmon. Not worth it.
Perfectly cooked soft boiled eggs. Wanton Mee and yong tau foo is good too! Support the old auntie.
Looks great on social media but not a fan of he cheesy ribs sorry.
Had the chicken kothu. It was fluffy, very tasty and well balanced. Homely vibe with dogs running around.
Paradise. The villa is so well designed, the staff are warm, friendly and hardworking. Wake up to monkeys, peacocks and squirrels in your backyard. This place is truly paradise.
Dinner for two, had the 1kg garlic crab and crab fried rice which was just nice. Crab was meaty, fresh and juicy. Perfect.
Try the black pork curry. The side dishes complement the pork so well; the rice is beautiful and fluffy. Quite overpriced but the service and ambience is nice.

formattedAddress: 2, Alfred House Rd (Off Alfred House Gardens)

tip.text: Had the most amazing spa here. Tried the stress relieving massage which focused on the shoulders and neck. They also used something like tiger balm which was perfection.
Try the Kuroson healthy don if you're a big fan of natto and okra! Fish is really fresh.
Tried the steak sandwich and aglio olio pasta. Would recommend the steak sandwich!! My usual is the green goddess pesto penne which is really awesome too!
DIY your usual teppei! Fresh generous chunks of seafood with toppings of your choice. My fav is salmon with baby scallops topped with avocado. Delish!
One of the better seafood places in Pulau Ubin. Try the sweet potato leaves, drunken prawn and steamed baby squid!
Ambience and service is 10/10. Food is alright. Starters: scallop & octopus salad were average. Mains: lobster linguine & beef were both done well. Dessert: Couldn't taste the alcohol in the tiramisu
Pepper lunch. Curry beef with egg. Sizzling hot yum yum.

formattedAddress: B2, Ngee Ann City Takashimaya (391 Orchard Rd.)

tip.text: Satay is big and flavourful.

formattedAddress: Stall 7, Adam Road Food Centre (2 Adam Road)

tip.text: Maggi goreng is decent. Value for money.

formattedAddress: Stall 11, Adam Road Food Centre (2 Adam Rd)

tip.text: Pork ribs noodles and chicken feet noodles is really good!!
Huge chunks of fish and seafood. Best mid day perk-me-up.
Hokkien Mee and satay (black shirt) is the best.

formattedAddress: Gardens by the Bay (18 Marina Gardens Drive #01-19)

tip.text: Both the Wagyu and regular Kalibi cuts are very good. Must try add ons are the garlic in foil and kimchi to go with the meat. Tip: cook the garlic in foil till soft, then bbq them. Best!
Try the crab pasta. It was very good with generous ratio of crab.
Their breakfast has rice which is awesome for any home sick asian. Rooms are new, clean and modern.
Chill place. Service is slow, food is decent. The little huts are a nice place to just relax and have a long lunch.
Hmm. Best hotpot in Singapore IMO. Nicer than HDL.

formattedAddress: #02-21 OneKM Shopping Mall (11 Tanjong Katong Road)

tip.text: Try the fish if you're not looking for anything too heavy. I find saveur to be consistently good. The angel hair pasta is a must try.
Presentation well done. Food tastes good too.
Good japanese food near the duomo. Great place for ladies to go after a long day of shopping amd just chill with umeshu and jap food.
Personalised cocktails! Good for a date or for guests visiting Singapore. Will not come back again as its slightly too pretentious and overpriced for my liking.
Natto, grated yam, ladies finger - love me some slimy food. Yum yum
Favourite breakfast buffet with amazing noodle station! Super wide breakfast selection. Rooms are clean and spacious.

contact.facebookName: Crowne Plaza Guangzhou City Centre  广州中心皇冠假日酒店

venue.name: 广州中心皇冠假日酒店 Crown Plaza Guangzhou City Centre

tip.text: To die for!! Favourite gelato at Duomo area.
Warm polipo salad with a glass of white. Fresh flavours lovely colours. Heard this is one of Tom Ford's favourite restaurant in Milan??
Must visit during durian season for some durian hunting. Fun and educational walk when the season is right.
Did the crater rim trek and would highly recommend that for a basic hike. Had the best time there even though there was a thunderstorm throughout the night.

venue.name: Mount Rinjani National Park (Taman Nasional Gunung Rinjani)

tip.text: Great place for a brisk walk or jog.
One of the best China Chinese food in singapore. Must try the kao yu and tomato egg. Flavours are well balanced and very authentic.
Food is mediocre but tableware and decor is very cool.
Insanely elegant place. Food is good and deco is amazing. Definetely a must-go in London.
Cant compare to the ones in japan but for singapore standard considered not bad. Personal favourite is the soy sauce with butter and egg coz the flavours are simple and good.

location.address: B2, Takashimaya Food Hall (Ngee Ann City)
formattedAddress: B2, Takashimaya Food Hall (Ngee Ann City) (391 Orchard Rd.)

tip.text: So so. The soft shell crab pasta was flavourful but too heavy.
Best place to stay at in Gili Meno. Rooms are amazing and the food is really good. Had the perfect time there.
Favourite is the tsukemen. Good on a hot day.

formattedAddress: #B1-44C, Raffles City Shopping Centre (252 North Bridge Rd.)

tip.text: Freeflow rice, soup and cabbage! The tonkatsu is consistently excellent and i would say the best tonkatsu chain in singapore.
One of the better chinese 烧烤 in Singapore.

venue.name: Liu Da Ma Charcoal BBQ Restaurant

tip.text: Best!! Try the lobster roll!! Never leave London without trying this place.
Decent rendition of taco rice.

formattedAddress: 中央4-11-5 (中央パークアベニュー)
location.crossStreet: 中央パークアベニュー

tip.text: Their best is still the boiled dumplings chased with a bottle of ice cold Kirin.
Comforting. A bottle of beer, a plate of eggplant and a bowl of rice. Unforgettable meal.
Nice view of the Duomo. Food is simple and fresh. Great place to chill with drinks when the weather is good.

formattedAddress: la Rinascente Duomo - 7° Piano (Food Market) (Via Santa Radegonda, 1)

tip.text: Oysters and prawns are good. Overall 7/10.

formattedAddress: #B1-44E, Raffles City Shopping Centre (252 North Bridge Rd.)

tip.text: The towering tauhu telor is a must must must try. Everything else is good too.
This place always hits the right spot especially after a chilly day in Paris. Anyone craving for Asian food in your travels, this is a must go.
Yummy and value for money. Attentive waitstaff.
Mediocre dim sum and the vibe is not chill.

formattedAddress: #B1-45/46, The Star Vista (1 Vista Exchange Green)

venue.name: Canton Paradise Teahouse 樂天小香港

tip.text: Good vibe and interesting selection of craft beers.
Salmon was pretty in pastel pink! Taste was 7/10.
Burgers are meh. The fish with polenta is good - nice crisp on the fish and the polenta is comforting. The quinoa salad is not bad too if you're feeling healthy.
Best Nasi Ayam ever!! Never disappoints. Tip: always ask for the crunchy bits!

formattedAddress: #01-41, Forum The Shopping Mall (583 Orchard Rd.)

tip.text: Authentic northern Thai food. Very delicious. Must try dishes are the grilled fish, Som tam, grilled fish, grilled pork.

venue.name: Nongkhai หนองคาย 隆开

tip.text: Awesome sushi. Really fresh and done well. Slightly pricey but very worth it!

venue.name: Sushi Kuu 壽司喰 (壽司喰)

tip.text: The noodles are fresh and comforting. Generous meat to noodle ratio!
Fresh and simple food done well. Must try dishes are the prawn paste chicken, steamed fish, hae zhor and bittergourd with egg. Crayfish is seasonal and you're lucky if you get the ones with roe!

venue.name: Zai Shun Curry Fish Head Seafood 载顺小食（夜市）

tip.text: Consistently good. Have been eating here since I was 5 and the taste is exactly the same. Love how they add minced garlic upon serving and I will always add extra vinegar for that extra kick!
Even though I think bingsus are just overpriced ice kachangs, this is of the best bingsus along Orchard belt. Didn't wait too long even though there was a queue. Personal favourite = soy milk bingsu.
Not as good as HDL but satisfying enough. Good selection of sauces/ingredients. Soup base slightly heavy on the MSG. Bar on level one serves as a good pre dinner waiting area with happy hour drinks.

venue.name: Shang Pin Hot Pot 尚品火锅

tip.text: Had the penne with zucchini and botargo (fish roe). It was the first time I tried botargo and it was very good. Simple flavours done well.
